Product Version     25.10    Cadence Design Systems, Inc.
reportSpecialRoute(25.10)                            reportSpecialRoute(25.10)

Name
       reportSpecialRoute - Reports the length of all RDL routes (SPECIALNETS)
       created with the fcroute command

Syntax
       reportSpecialRoute

       [-help]

       [<reportName>]

       [-center_line]

       [-net <netName>]

       [-interposer_ndr_check

          [-exclude_nets <netName>]]

       [-interposer_route

          [-exclude_nets <netName>]]

       [-interposer_route

          [[-interposer_layers <layerName>]

           [-interposer_route_constraint_file <ircFileName>]]]

       [-interposer_shielding_ratio

          [-exclude_nets <netName>]]

       [[ [-by_layer]

          [-highlight45layer <layerName>]

          [-lengththreshold <value>]

          [-resfile <resFileName>]

          [-selected]

          [-summary]

          [-wire_segment]

          [-wirelength]   ]

        | [-interposer_ndr_check ]

        | [-interposer_route ]

        | [-interposer_shielding_ratio ]]

       Reports  the  length  of  all RDL routes (SPECIALNETS) created with the
       fcroute command. This includes  support  for  Manhattan  and  45-degree
       routes.  You  can  report the wire length of each SPECIALNET and report
       the SPECIALNETS that are greater in length than the specified threshold
       value.

       Use the -by_layer and -wire_segment options to  report  the  width  and
       length of the special nets per layer and wire segment.

Parameters
       -help  Outputs  a  brief description that includes type and default in-
              formation for each reportSpecialRoute parameter.

              For a detailed description of the command and all of its parame-
              ters, use the man command:

              man reportSpecialRoute

       -by_layer
              Reports on layers of each special net. Here's a sample format of
              the report when the -by_layer option is specified:

       -center_line
              Specifies that routing length is calculated by center line. That
              is, the sum of wire  center  line  is  used  to  calculate  wire
              length. Without this parameter, the routing length is calculated
              as sum of wire segments.

       -exclude_nets <netName>
              Specifies the net names to be excluded.

              This option can be used only if -interposer_route is specified.

       -highlight45layer <layerName>
              Highlights  (in  yellow)  all nets with 45-degree routing on the
              specified layer in the design display area.

       -interposer_layers <layerName>
              Specifies the interposer layers. Use this option to  report  the
              maximum  and  minimum routing length from tap via to tap via and
              from bump to tap via by layer.

              This option can be used only if -interposer_route is specified.

       -interposer_ndr_check
              Specifies that the tool should check for interposer routing  NDR
              violations  and  incomplete  shielding.  If any violation is de-
              tected, the report includes information on the net,  layer,  and
              location  of the violation and a marker is displayed in the Vio-
              lation Browser. By default, the -interposer_ndr_check  check  is
              performed for each interposer route net; you can use the -net or
              -exclude_nets options to limit the check to specific nets.

              You  can  check  interposer  routing  NDR  rules  by using dbGet
              $<net>.interposer*. If no interposer rules have been defined for
              a net, the checker will skip the NDR check for that net.

              For example, to check interposer routing signal route rule, use:

              dbGet $net.interposerTrunkRules

       -interposer_route
              Reports the interposer route statistics, including maximum, min-
              imum, and average wire length of the interposer routing. report-
              SpecialRoute reads the constraints defined by  setIntegRouteCon-
              straint  to  decide  which  nets are in one group. The  setInte-
              gRouteConstraint constraints are either obtained from the DB  or
              can   be   specified   through  a  file  by  using  the  -inter-
              poser_route_constraint_file option.

              The report format is as shown below:

              ### Header ###

              ### Total Nets of Interposer Route ###

              Total nets: <total nets number>

              Layer: Layer_name

              Net with Max wire length: <net name + net length>

              Net with Min wire length: <net name + net length>

              Average wire length:

              ### Net Group <group_name1> ###

              Total nets: <nets number in group>

              Layer: Layer_name

              Net with Max wire length:

                       <net name> :

                       net length :

                       Euclidean distance:

                       Manhattan distance:

              Net with Min wire length:

                       <net name> :

                       net length :

                       Euclidean distance:

                       Manhattan distance:

              Average wire length:

              Nets name:

              ### Net Group <group_name2> ###

              Total nets: <nets number in group>

              Layer: Layer_name

              Net with Max length: <net name + net length>

              Net with Min length: <net name + net length>

              Average wire length:

              Nets name:

              The <group_name> of the nets is obtained from  setIntegRouteCon-
              straint  -name <group_name>. If -name is not specified, the tool
              uses a number to mark the net group.

              For example: ### Net Group <1> ###

       -interposer_route_constraint_file <ircFileName>
              Specifies the name of the interposer route constraint file. This
              option can be used only if -interposer_route is specified.

       -interposer_shielding_ratio
              Checks and reports the same-layer and interlayer shielding ratio
              of interposer routing nets.

              * Checks the same-layer and interlayer shielding separately.

              * Checks only the  nets  with  the  route_interposer_trunk_rules
                property.

              * For  shielding  ratio,  the  wire length is calculated by wire
                center line, not by the sum of wire segment lengths.

              Use the -net option to limit the check to specific nets.

              For a sample report, see Examples.

       -lengththreshold <value>
              Reports on the SPECIALNETS that are greater in length  than  the
              specified  value.  These  values  are  listed in the output file
              specified by <reportName> and the routes are highlighted in  the
              GUI.

       -net <netName>
              Reports  on  the  wire  length of each SPECIALNET fora specified
              net.

              Note: You must use this parameter in conjunction with the -wire-
              length or -lengththreshold parameters.

       <reportName>
              Specifies the report file name. The default  file  name  is  sp-
              wire.rpt.

       -resfile <resFileName>
              Specifies  the  resistance  file name (fcroute.res) generated by
              fcroute if srouteFCReport <file name> is specified in the config
              file and highlights the violated nets on GUI when the resistance
              does not match the max  resistance  constraint  defined  in  the
              fcroute constraint file.

       -selected
              Reports  the  length of the selected wire segments for each spe-
              cial net.

       -summary
              Summarizes the wire length and VIAs for special nets.  Here's  a
              sample format of the report when -summary is specified:

       -wire_segment
              Reports  on the wire segments of each special net. Here's a sam-
              ple format of the report when -wire_segment is specified:

       -wirelength
              Reports on the wire length of each SPECIALNET.

Examples
              * The following command reports the wire length of each SPECIAL-
                NET and lists it in the spwire.rpt report file:

                reportSpecialRoute spwire.rpt -wirelength

